#McAninch, Carl -  Mid Term program

print ('Planet Express Delivery Time Calculator')
print ('')

planet = input('What is the name of the planet?')
print ('')

distance = input ('How many parsecs away?')
distance = float (distance)
print('')

packages = input('How many packages?')
packages = int(packages)
print ('')
weight = input ('How many tons does each package weigh?')
weight = float (weight)

if (packages >= 10 and packages % 2 == 1.0):
  print ('')
  print ('')
  print ('Warning: Adjusting package count to', packages + 1)
  packages = packages + 1


trip1 = (packages * weight * distance + distance)



if (distance < 1 ):
  print('')
  print('')
  print('Error', planet, 'must be one or more parsecs away.')
elif(packages < 1 ):
  print ('Error: The ship must carry at least one package.')
elif(weight <=0 ):
  print('Error: The package weight', weight, 'is too light.')


else:
  print ('The total cargo weight is', packages * weight, 'ton(s).')
  print  ('The trip to', planet, 'will take', trip1 , 'minutes.')
  print ('The trip back to Earth will take', distance, 'minutes.')
  trip2 = (trip1+ distance)
  print ('The total trip time is', trip2, 'minutes.')


print ('')

if (planet == 'Robot Planet'):
  print ('Also, Bender is Great!')
